                    <h3 class="head-sm fw-400" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-duration="2000">Reclamation</h3>
                    <p class="text-md mt-5" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-duration="2000">Reclamation rules are very strict, and require us to restore the landscape as closely to its former condition as possible. The baseline studies we have undertaken will be used to ensure this happens. As part of the permitting process, we will be required to post a cash reclamation bond with the federal government, which will only be redeemable if we complete the required work. This cash bond will be determined at a later date, and is likely to run into millions of dollars, as it is an estimate of how much it will cost to reclaim the mine in the future.</p>
                    <p class="text-md mt-5 mb-0" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-duration="2000">
                        We have every intention of overseeing this work to a high standard
                        ourselves. This will require recontouring and revegetating the area with native plant life, as specified in the permit. If we fail to complete the work as required, we will forfeit the bond, and the cash will be used by federal agencies to do the work instead.
                    </p>
                </div>
